		Netropy Server - serving JavaScript



$(document).ready(function () {
  $("div#animate").addClass("ohmy").show("slow");
  $("div#animate a").click(function () {
		$("div#jquery-plug").addClass("ohmy").animate({
	    height: 'toggle',
	    opacity: 'show',
		}, "slow");
	});
	$("div#jquery-plug em").click(function () {
		$("div#feedback").addClass("ohmy").animate({
	    height: 'toggle',
	    opacity: 'show',
		}, "slow");
  });
});




Another minimal test...


			... using the jQuery JavaScript library embedded in the blueprint of this system.




jQuery is the JavaScript framework of choice for this platform, due to its extremely small footprint (only ~16Kb).
				Update Easter 2016: Note that was written back in 2009, meanwhile the library has evolved considerably. Also alternatives such as zepto.js 
				have emerged, with footprint less than 10kB.


Return to the demos.






